Book written by American journalist 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- A journalist of Washington Times pulled up the DPRK over "suspected nuclear development" in his book, allegedly based on "secret information" of the U.S. Central Intelligence Agency (CIA).
   Commenting on it, Rodong Sinmun today says:   The United States has long been loudmouthed about the nonexistent "suspicion of nuclear development" by the DPRK, in a bid to attain its insidious purpose, but its falsity has been fully revealed with  the passage of time.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This journalist  was so mean that he referred to "nuclear suspicion" on the basis of the CIA's "secret information."   The CIA is the general headquarters of worldwide terrorism and a master of intrigues and fabrication. It is engaged in terrorism and plotting to do harm to any country, if it stands against or is unacceptable to the United States.   After all,  the argument about "nuclear suspicion" of the DPRK  turned out to be false because it is based on "secret information" provided by the CIA, a master-hand in reversing black and white.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Dignity of a pressman is guaranteed by objectivity and impartiality. This indicates that the journalist of Washington Times has lost his dignity as he provoked the DPRK with false information.

Truth about test-firing of new missile in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- The propaganda department of the central committee of the National Democratic Front of South  Korea (NDFSK) made public an indictment titled "We uncover the truth of the test-firing of a new missile in South  Korea" on May 20, according to the Seoul-based radio Voice of National Salvation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The South  Korean authorities recently test-fired a missile of new type developed by the South  Korean National Defence Science Institute at the Anhung General Missile Firing Range on the west coast of Korea. Announcing that it was the missile "Hyonmu", which  was already developed and completed in 1987 and deployed in the forward area along the truce line to be ready to go into action, they asserted that this was a test for developing "materials for its wing and other parts."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The NDFSK in the indictment said:   The authorities argued that the recent test-firing was made to "develop parts" 12 years after their successful development of "Hyonmu" with 176-250 km range. This is a sophism which can convince no one.
The South  Korean authorities have escalated the missile development since early in the 1970s and developed and completed "Paekgom," "Hyonmu" and other missiles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Having worked out a plan to develop a missile with a range of 500 km by the year 1995 and a missile with a range of 1,500 km by the year 2000, they have pushed ahead with it in real earnest by employing such crafty methods as allotted,   research and development and joint production at the National Defense Science Institute and Aero- Space Institute under the pretext of "development of space industry."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The U.S. asserted that it is a missile of new type the range of which could be well beyond 300 km in case it is fully charged with propellant fuel after photographing the course of the missile test-firing by an intelligence satellite.  And the "Minister of National Defence" said he could not disclose its actual flight-capacity because it was a military secret. This clearly proves that the National Defence Science Institute developed and test-fired a missile of new type by increasing its efficiency and lengthening the range of the existing missile "Hyonmu." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The test-firing is a product of the reckless and provocative anti-north confrontation policy of the present "government" and its moves for a war against the north. This proves that the United States is sticking to its double standards as regards its missile policy toward the Korean peninsula.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Although the United States ostensibly restricted the missile development in South  Korea to the range of 180 km, it has encouraged South  Korea's missile development by providing technology of manufacturing satellites and developing carrier rockets as well as missile designs and all kinds of equipment for its development and systematically increased the capacity of the "ROK" army for a war against the north.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   If it continues applying double standards to the Korean peninsula  the DPRK-U.S. missile talks now under way will come to a rupture and this will increase the military tensions and danger of war on the peninsula.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It is the heinous ambition of the Kim Dae Jung "government" to step up the missile development under the U.S. patronage and support behind the scene, join the ranks of semi-nuclear weapon states such as Japan in a few years to come and have a military edge in the inter-Korean relations to overpower the north.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The reality clearly shows that though South  Korea makes any weapon with the  help of the United States, it will not be for the nation and the people but bring only calamities to them as it will be under the U.S. control and used for the execution of a war against the north as long as the U.S. colonial policy toward South  Korea remains unchanged.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The present "government" should give up a foolish and base ambition to stifle the north by developing new type weapons and take the road of national reconciliation and great national unity at an early date.

Invincible army under brilliant commander
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- the Korean People's Army (KPA) has grown to be an invincible army  strong enough to wipe out any enemy at a stroke.   The KPA is highly honored to have the great leader Kim Jong Il, who has far-sighted wisdom, tested leadership ability, matchless grit and outstanding strategy, in high esteem as its Supreme Commander.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The anti-socialist moves and war fever of the imperialist allied forces against the DPRK have reached the highest pitch in recent five years.
    Last year the DPRK was in a touch-and-go situation  in which a war may break out any time following the announcement of "5027 operation plan" by the bellicose U.S. military quarters.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    A spokesman for the KPA general staff in a statement clarified its hard-line stand that the KPA would meet the challenge of the U.S. aggression  forces by a fatal blow.    Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il long ago made clear an immutable truth that  peace and socialism are guaranteed by the power of the gun,  army is the party, people and state, and socialism  can be defended and national reunification  can be achieved by a strong army.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    He defined revolutionary leadership with priority given to the army as a leadership way of revolution and has exerted primary efforts to strengthen the  revolutionary armed forces, bringing about a signal success in army building.   In recent four years he inspected more than 330 People's Army units, covering  46,280 km.    Among them were forefront units including those defending Panmunjom, Mt. Thaedok, and heights 351 and 1211.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    Whenever moves of the enemy grew serious and the situation of the country became strained, he inspected combined units and units of the People's Army to take operational steps to provide against the reckless provocations of the enemy and encourage the People's Army soldiers to struggle and feats.    His revolutionary leadership with priority given to the army is the source that made it possible for the KPA to grow to be an invincible army.

Reminiscences "With the Century" published in Nepal
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- Vol. 6 of part 1 the anti-Japanese revolution of the President Kim Il Sung's reminiscences "With the Century" was published at the Samjana Publishing House of Nepal on the occasion of Sun's Day.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is written on the front page of the recently published reminiscences that President Kim Il Sung's august name is shining for ever in the course of the revolutionary struggle of the world progressive people and the immortal Juche idea created by him indicates the road to be followed by the revolutionary struggle of the people who aspire after independence.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is also noted that vol.6 of part 1 the anti-Japanese revolution of the reminiscences "With the Century", the immortal revolutionary biography which comprehensively deals with the President's life of struggle and valuable experience has been published in Nepalese on the occasion of Sun's Day.

S. Korean trade unionists' struggle supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- Working people of the DPRK have met to extend  support and solidarity to the South  Korean workers' struggle for vital rights and democracy. 
   Rallies to support the struggle of the members of railway, construction, metal, passenger transport and hospital workers unions of South  Korea were held at the West Pyongyang Locomotive Unit, the Central District Public Building Construction Office, the Pyongyang Steel Works, the 1st bus office of the Pyongyang City Passenger Transport Management Bureau and Pyongyang City People's Hospital no. 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Speakers at the rallies noted that the struggle of South  Korean unionists was a just one for vital rights and an eruption of their surging resentment and wrath upon the South  Korean authorities who have brought greater sufferings and misfortunes to workers and other people through their flunkeyist and anti-social misrule. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Accusing the South  Korean ruling quarters of going ahead with "re-structuring," indifferent to the demand of the workers, they declared:    The South  Korean ruling quarters are arresting leading members of trade unions and workers after branding their  just struggle as "illegal" and "violent" and hatching a plot to "take legal actions against" all of them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They bitterly denounced the fascist group's suppression of the labor movement, saying that such truculent anti-social fascist group as the South  Korean authorities can be found nowhere else in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  They called on the South  Korean workers to strengthen the inter-regional, inter-departmental and  inter-trade union solidarity struggle and  the struggle for solidarity with students, peasants and people of other strata and carry on a more stubborn struggle to achieve vital rights and democracy to the end.

Investment in electric power industry annually increases
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- The DPRK earmarked funds, 15 percent greater than last year, for electric power industry this year.     It will direct big efforts to operating power plants in full capacity, step up the construction of large hydro-power plants and build new large  power plants. Minor power stations will be built on a large scale  along rivers and streams in localities to meet the need of electric power in cities and counties and realize rural electrification on a high level.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The construction of power plants is being pushed forward throughout  the country.
   The builders of the Anbyon Youth Power Station are substantially carrying on the project, concentrating all efforts  on the project after finishing the initial water storage.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The builders of the Namgang Power Plant are stepping up hundreds of metres of parapet and embankment projects.    The builders of the Thaechon power plants nos. 2 and 3 have finished the production makeshift project which is equal to the construction of a big factory, while pushing ahead with excavation for  the main dam.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Last year the state allocated for the power industry 6 percent bigger funds than the previous year to increase generating capacity.    As a result, the construction of large hydro-power plants was accelerated and 5,000 minor power stations have been built across the country.   The prospect of the country's power industry development  is very good.   Deposits of anthracite, brown and other coal are abundant and there are thousands of big and small  rivers and streams. The country is rich in resources of tidal power, wind power and atomic energy.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The state is exerting sustained efforts to make an effective use of all resources and expand and consolidate power bases of the country,  a breakthrough in building a powerful socialist nation and life line of the national economy.

S. Korea's dangerous war exercises
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- The South Korean war hawks declared they would hold a "command post exercise" under the provocative code name of "Amnokgang exercise" for 6 days from today. Commenting on this, a news analyst of rodong sinmun today says:   The exercise to be participated in by military officers above army corps-level is not a "defensive exercise" but a preliminary war gamble, a mock war on the eve of a real war.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The exercise, part of moves to unify the military command system according to the U.S. "5027 operation plan", a plan for a second war of aggression on Korea, is a dangerous war gamble that has made provocation of a war against the north a fait accompli. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK does not want war but it is always merciless to provokers, the commentary says, adding that if they encroach upon even an inch of the  territory of the DPRK, the Korean People's Army will never miss the opportunity to deal a telling blow to the aggressors.

Greetings to Nepalese Foreign Minister
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- DPRK Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun sent a message of greetings to Foreign Minister of the Kingdom of Nepal Girija Prasad Koirala on the occasion of the 25th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between the two countries.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message said that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries have developed satisfactorily in various fields for the last 25 years.   It expressed the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries will develop on to a higher stage in accordance with the desire of the two peoples to build an independent and prosperous  new century.
